## ⚙️ Local Setup

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.11+
- Node.js 18+
- Git

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/sentimental-drive.git
cd sentimental-drive
```

### 2. Backend setup

```bash
# Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv

# Activate (Windows)
venv\Scripts\activate

# Activate (macOS/Linux)
source venv/bin/activate

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 3. Environment variables

```bash
# Copy the example file
cp .env.example .env
```

Edit `.env` and fill in your credentials:

```env
# Angel One SmartAPI (optional — app works without it via yfinance fallback)
ANGEL_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
ANGEL_CLIENT_CODE=your_client_code
ANGEL_PIN=your_mpin
ANGEL_TOTP_SECRET=your_totp_base32_secret

# NewsAPI (optional — improves sentiment analysis)
NEWSAPI_KEY=your_newsapi_key

# ML Model (set to 1 to use trained XGBoost, 0 for rule-based fallback)
USE_TRAINED_MODEL=1
```

> **Note:** The app works without Angel One and NewsAPI credentials using yfinance historical data and basic sentiment rules.

### 4. Download stock data (first time only)

```bash
# Download historical data for all 100 NIFTY stocks
python scripts/download_nifty100.py

# Build the combined training dataset
python scripts/create_combined_dataset.py
```

### 5. Start the backend

```bash
python -m uvicorn backend.main:app --reload --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000
```

Backend runs at: `http://localhost:8000`

API docs at: `http://localhost:8000/docs`

### 6. Start the frontend

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

Frontend runs at: `http://localhost:5173`

