## 🤖 Machine Learning

### Dataset

| Property | Value |
|---|---|
| Stocks covered | 100 NIFTY companies |
| Total rows | 138,000+ |
| Date range | 2020 – present |
| Features | 22 (technical + sentiment) |
| Target | Binary: 1 = UP, 0 = DOWN |
| Train/test split | 80/20 chronological (no shuffle) |

### Features used

```
Price:      Close, High, Low, Open, Volume
Returns:    Return (daily), Price_chg_5d
Trend:      SMA_10, SMA_20, SMA_50, SMA_200
Momentum:   RSI, MACD, MACD_signal, Momentum
Volatility: Bollinger Upper/Lower/Width/Pct, ATR, Volatility
Volume:     Vol_MA_10, Volume_change
Sentiment:  Sentiment_score (VADER compound)
```

### Model performance

| Model | Accuracy | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Random Forest (baseline) | ~50% | No hyperparameter tuning |
| XGBoost (production) | ~55–58% | Trained on 138k rows |
| Rule-based fallback | — | Used when model unavailable |

### Signal logic

```python
if prediction == UP and RSI < 70 and Close > SMA_20 and MACD > MACD_signal:
    signal = "BUY"
elif prediction == DOWN and RSI > 30 and Close < SMA_20 and MACD < MACD_signal:
    signal = "SELL"
else:
    signal = "HOLD"
```

---

## 📊 Backtest Results (TCS — 1478 trading days)

| Metric | Value |
|---|---|
| Total trades | 867 |
| Win rate | 46.14% |
| Market return (Buy & Hold) | +80.88% |
| Strategy return | -22.72% |
| Sharpe ratio | -0.159 |
| Max drawdown | -30.93% |

> **Note:** Raw ML signal accuracy alone is insufficient for profitable trading. Production use requires risk management, position sizing, stop-loss logic, and transaction cost modeling on top of the model signals.

